extends layout.pug


block content 
  article.grid-container.portfolio-intro
    div

      //- Add a title or heading like My Portfolio, or Hey, Potential Employers, or Let's make the web great together! 
      h1.lobsterFont My Portfolio

      //- Add a description for your portfolio, what this project is, it's purpose, what it's suppossed to accomplish, etc. 
      p.lead.text-light
        | These projects were completed during the 5 first units of the Techdegree Program. The Full Stack JavaScript Techdegree is meant to train students in HTML, CSS, JavaScript, NodeJS and Express, and this lets me practice and shows off my mastery of these fundamental skills.
  article.grid-container.portfolio-index
    
    .grid-x.grid-margin-x.small-up-2.medium-up-2.large-up-3

      //- Use the Pug `each` iterator to create a project img, title and link in the markup for each of the projects you are showcasing.  
      
      //- Use a combination of interpolation and template literals as needed to dynamically generate the routes in the href, as well as the img's src and the projects title.
      
      //- Here's what the Pug for each project example should look like. 

      each val, index in project
        .cell            
            a(href= "project/" + index)
                .boundary
                    img.thumbnail.projectImg(src= project[index].image_urls[0])
                h5.letterPopUp= project[index].project_name